\begin_layout Standard
Asteroid surveys in the past have been biased towards larger, brigher objects,
 rarely being able to resolve asteroids dimmer than 22nd absolute magnitude
 because of technological limitations
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Jedicke2002AsteroidsIII"

\end_inset

.
 A new, multi-year program started in August of 2013 called the Mission
 Accessible Near-Earth Object Survey (MANOS) seeks to leverage advances
 in observing capabilities to characterize asteroid targets that would have
 been previously impossible to do, with a focus on targets that would be
 accessible by space missions utilizing conventional chemical propulsion.
 
